          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Structured Settlement Claimants Rights Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill allows a claimant in a civil action in federal court to retain a structured settlement broker to negotiate a schedule of payments for an amount previously agreed to be paid by the defendant in satisfaction of a judgment or settlement. The same right is afforded to parties in administrative agency adjudications.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-04-10T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
